translated: Ernst David Edsbäcker was born on April 30, 1890 in Färnebo, Värmland. He was the first-born child of Carl Jansson and Maria Nilsson. He married Anna-Lena Magnusson in 1915 and they had six children: Margareta (born 1919), Birgitta (born 1920), Ingalill (born 1928), Marianne (born 1930), Karl Arne (born 1915), and Yngve (born 1917). Edsbäcker was the managing director for several companies, including Tjust Träexport AB, AB Swedish Propsexport Ltd, AB Stallarholmens Såg & Hyvleri, AB Turinge Bränntorv, and Åseda Industri AB. He was also a commissioner for the Västerviks exhibition in 1933, a member of the city council from 1930, and a member of the board of directors for Västerviks Sparbank from 1931 to 1940. Edsbäcker was also a member of the Freemason Order and traveled to Finland, Norway, Denmark, Germany, Belgium, and England. He received the Order of the Vasa in 1933.
